article.headline: Georgia 105, South Carolina State 60
article.story: ATHENS, Ga. (AP) -- Mike Mercer found the range from beyond the 3-point line, hitting five treys en route to a career-high 26-point effort in Georgia's 105-60 victory over South Carolina State Tuesday. Mercer missed his first eight 3-point tries this season and was 2 for 13 entering the game. Terrence Woodbury and Takais Brown came off the bench to score 13 points apiece for Georgia (3-1). Travis Jones led South Carolina State (0-3) with 12 points. Georgia hit 12 3-pointers and reached the century mark for the second straight game. Georgia shot 62 percent from the field, compared to 34 percent for South Carolina State. Georgia put the game away early. South Carolina State went six minutes between field goals early in the first half. Meanwhile, Georgia mounted a 16-3 run to take a 25-7 lead with 9:54 to go in the half on Albert Jackson's putback. Georgia hit seven 3-pointers in the first half, including three by Mercer, who had 13 at the half. Georgia led 51-28 at halftime. South Carolina State fared much better in its first game against Southeastern Conference opposition this year. They opened the season at South Carolina, pushing the Gamecocks in a 55-52 loss.
